scGPT
-----
Homepage: https://github.com/bowang-lab/scGPT
License: MIT License (Copyright (c) 2022 suber)

Clifti-GPT imports the scGPT Python package at runtime and adapts the scGPT
transformer architecture for federated single-cell analysis. Pretrained scGPT
checkpoints (e.g. whole-human `best_model.pt`, `vocab.json`, `args.json`) are
third-party assets: they are not shipped in this repository and must be
downloaded separately from the scGPT project under its license.

When using Clifti-GPT, also cite:
  Cui, H. et al. scGPT: toward building a foundation model for single-cell
  multi-omics using generative AI. Nature Methods 21, 1470–1480 (2024).
  https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-024-02201-0

Per-dataset init weights published on Zenodo (10.5281/zenodo.20489646) are
state_dict snapshots taken after loading scGPT pretrained weights and before
Clifti-GPT fine-tuning. Redistribution of those files should retain scGPT
attribution and comply with the scGPT license.
